Ran Nashville Half Marathon
description: Yesterday, I was someone who had never run a half-marathon before. Today, I’m someone who has run a half-marathon, and also someone whose feet and ankles have magically aged forty years overnight. One could argue that the person I am today isn’t objectively any better than the person I was yesterday. And they would be right, except for the fact that I like the person I am today, and maybe that’s all that really matters. The person I am today is someone who did something they couldn’t quite do, and were a little bit afraid of. Tomorrow, I’ll be someone else.
